    Initial groove implementation

    kbowers-jump merged to firedancer-io/firedancer at 2025-02-18 22:18:22

    Initial groove implementation - base: error codes (harmonized with the concurrent data structures), key type (256-bit public keys), memory mapped HPC I/O friendly data block specification (512 byte blocks that are 512 byte aligned). - meta: concurrent key-metadata store. This is a thin wrapper around fd_map_slot_para using spatially local key-metadata pairs. Allows for fast massively parallel testing of account existence with details about account size and where the account can be found (for latency / bandwidth / scheduling purposes). - volume: This is mostly a thin wrapper around fd_pool_para to provide a lock free pool of 1GiB sized volumes that can be stored in a mixture of DRAM (preferablly gigabyte page backed), memory mapped 1GiB files on NVMe, memory mapped 1 GiB files on SSD, etc. Some basic operations for added and removing volumes from a pool while not stalling or otherwise impacting ongoing operations are provided. - data: concurrent value store. This is lockfree massively parallel allocator similar to fd_alloc but instead of being backed by wksp, it is backed by volumes. Allocator size classes have been tuned for account sized allocations and the data block granularity. Additionally, the fd_alloc algorithm was tweaked such that parameters used for all allocations are discoverable, all allocations can be independently tagged (which also means there are non-trivial zero sized allocations) and all allocations are independently discoverable. - top level: Currently just pulls all the above components together. Also added a thread turnstile primitive to fd_util_base.h (included in the c.vim syntax highlighter), an API for getting the least signficant bit from a primitive integer type to fd_bits.h, cleaned up a comment in fd_bits.h and cleaned up a comment in fd_map_para.c.

    by kbowers-jump
